HEADWORD: Tiewig
<hw>Tie"wig`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wig having a tie or
ties, or one having some of the curls tied up; also, a wig tied upon the
head.</def> <rj><au>Wright. V. Knox.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

